This article is a transcript of remarks made by President Trump in the Roosevelt Room of the White House. The President is thanking and honoring the first responders who helped during the bridge collapse on I-85 in Atlanta. He praises their bravery and quick action, and pledges support for law enforcement and public safety. The President also discusses the importance of infrastructure and his commitment to funding a nationwide infrastructure program. Secretary of Transportation Elaine Chao also speaks, highlighting the heroism of the first responders and the quick repairs that will be made to the bridge. The President also briefly mentions a recent military operation in Afghanistan and the situation with North Korea.